President Barack Obama has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the attack in Nice, France that occurred on July 14, 2016. The flag will be flown at half-staff at the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on July 19, 2016. The same honor will be given at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.